www.jlpzj.net
本字幕仅供学习交流，严禁用于商业用途
========================
翻译, 校订: Hugh


2
00:00:08.792 --> 00:00:11.352
埃尔顿•约翰到松林制片厂的时间是…
Elton John, up at Pinewood on--


3
00:00:11.495 --> 00:00:13.190
- 什么时候来着? - 12号
- What's the date? - The 12th of--


4
00:00:13.330 --> 00:00:14.592
3月12号
Twelfth of March.


5
00:00:14.731 --> 00:00:18.167
这里是20… 30帧分轨中心
It's me, split track, 20-- Thirty-frame center track.


6
00:00:18.802 --> 00:00:20.394
就是这个调
There's the tone.


7
00:00:26.409 --> 00:00:27.433
请安静
Quiet, please.


8
00:00:33.769 --> 00:00:41.707
1984-1994十年间，一场融天时地利人和的完美风暴
彻底改变了整个动画行业的面貌


9
00:00:43.393 --> 00:00:45.020
开始
Here we go.


10
00:00:48.777 --> 00:00:51.609
埃尔顿·约翰爵士

11
00:00:50.767 --> 00:00:52.382
那是1994年的春天
It was the spring of 1994


12
00:00:52.383 --> 00:00:55.033
我们即将完成狮子王的制作
and we were just finishing The Lion King,


13
00:00:55.171 --> 00:00:56.729
这部电影好评如潮
which would go on to earn great reviews


14
00:00:56.873 --> 00:01:00.604
并赚取了7.5亿美元的票房
and about three-quarters of a billion dollars at the box office.


15
00:01:00.744 --> 00:01:03.577
对迪斯尼的新员工来说 这是个好消息
Not bad for a group of artists who were kicked off the Disney lot


16
00:01:03.713 --> 00:01:07.547
该片也算是挽回了2D动画江河日下的颓势
and an art form that was given up for dead just ten years earlier.


17
00:01:13.089 --> 00:01:14.249
我是狮子王的制片人
I produced The Lion King


18
00:01:14.391 --> 00:01:16.951
当时, 剧组人员即将举行首发见面会
and the cast-and-crew premiere was coming up fast.


19
00:01:17.093 --> 00:01:20.789
按照惯例, 大家会逐一登台致感谢词
It was tradition for all of us to get up on-stage and give warm thank-you speeches.


20
00:01:20.931 --> 00:01:24.697
这一次, 我决定把致谢演讲拍下来
But this time I decided to film all the speeches instead.


21
00:01:25.869 --> 00:01:27.837
开始拍了?
You are rolling?


22
00:01:27.971 --> 00:01:29.939
- 是的 - 好
- Yeah. - Okay.


23
00:01:30.774 --> 00:01:36.610
在公司的各项业务中, 很明显…
With all the many varied businesses this company is in, it is clear--


24
00:01:32.498 --> 00:01:38.584
迈克尔·埃斯纳
迪斯尼公司CEO


25
00:01:36.746 --> 00:01:41.274
动画将日渐成为我们的灵魂与核心
It becomes clearer every day that animation is its soul, heart,


26
00:01:41.418 --> 00:01:44.910
是我们的主体业务
and most of its body parts.


27
00:01:45.221 --> 00:01:48.418
过去这些年, 你们表现得很出色
You guys have done an unbelievable job over the last decade,


28
00:01:48.558 --> 00:01:53.237
完成了佳作狮子王, 推动了公司发展
culminating in Lion King, in pushing forward the company,


29
00:01:53.238 --> 00:01:56.391
彰显了文化的魅力与艺术的气质
the culture and the quality of artistry.


30
00:01:56.533 --> 00:02:01.698
我要代表我本人, 公司董事会, 股东, 以及我的孩子
Congratulations from me, from anybody who is not on this tape,


31
00:02:01.838 --> 00:02:04.966
向你们表示祝贺
from our board, our shareholders and my children.


32
00:02:05.108 --> 00:02:06.166
恭喜大家
Congratulations.


33
00:02:06.443 --> 00:02:08.308
谢谢 谢谢大家
Thank you. Thanks, everybody.


34
00:02:08.445 --> 00:02:12.279
感谢大家奉献的精彩作品
Thank you to everybody for another absolutely incredible job


35
00:02:12.415 --> 00:02:15.509
希望能再接再厉, 再创辉煌
on another marvelous movie on the way to the next great movie.


36
00:02:15.652 --> 00:02:17.517
外界看来, 这一切都很完美
To an outsider, it looked like a perfect world.


37
00:02:17.654 --> 00:02:19.019
但是在幕后
But backstage,


38
00:02:19.155 --> 00:02:20.884
气氛已十分紧张
the tension had reached a peak.


39
00:02:21.024 --> 00:02:22.082
谢谢, 可以了吗?
Thank you. Okay?


40
00:02:23.593 --> 00:02:25.993
尽管我们刚取得了前所未有的成功
Even though it was the moment of our greatest success,


41
00:02:26.129 --> 00:02:28.893
但已经是山雨欲来风满楼了
the wheels were coming off the car.


42
00:02:29.032 --> 00:02:31.830
下面我来细讲故事的来龙去脉
This is the story of how we got there.


43
00:02:32.193 --> 00:02:36.751
片名：唤醒睡美人

44
00:02:39.776 --> 00:02:41.368
让我们回到80年代初期
Let's back up to the early '80s


45
00:02:41.511 --> 00:02:44.537
加州伯班克市的迪斯尼制片场
on the Disney Studio lot in Burbank, California.


46
00:02:44.681 --> 00:02:47.616
我们的乐队正向同事们传递着假日的喜悦
The animation band is spreading its holiday cheer to the employees


47
00:02:47.751 --> 00:02:50.379
一如既往, 主奏乐器是班卓琴和单簧琴
with banjos and jew's harps, as was the tradition.


48
00:02:51.021 --> 00:02:52.407
右边这个人就是我
And that's me on the right,


49
00:02:52.408 --> 00:02:54.513
正用贝斯弹着铃儿响叮当
trying to play"Jingle Bells" On the bass.


50
00:02:54.658 --> 00:02:57.525
与同龄人一样, 我是看着迪斯尼电影长大的
Like so many of us, I grew up on a diet of Disney films.


51
00:02:57.661 --> 00:02:59.390
每过四年, 我就会像朝圣一样
And every four years, I'd make a pilgrimage


52
00:02:59.529 --> 00:03:03.158
奔向露天影院一睹迪斯尼最新大作的风采
to the drive-in theater to see their latest animated masterpiece.


53
00:03:03.299 --> 00:03:05.164
20岁时, 我在迪斯尼工作室觅得一份差事
When I was 20, I got a job at the studio


54
00:03:05.301 --> 00:03:07.633
负责给动画制作人端茶送水
delivering artwork and coffee to the animators


55
00:03:07.771 --> 00:03:10.797
为此我已感觉欣喜若狂
and I felt like I won the lottery.


56
00:03:12.208 --> 00:03:14.073
这就是沃特建的房子
This was the house that Walt built.


57
00:03:14.210 --> 00:03:18.340
沃特•迪斯尼, 好莱坞骄子, 打造迪斯尼乐园的天才
Walt Disney, the toast of Hollywood, the genius behind Disneyland


58
00:03:18.481 --> 00:03:21.917
还制作了第一部动画电影: 白雪公主
and the producer behind the first animated feature, Snow White.


59
00:03:23.053 --> 00:03:25.920
到了五十年代, 沃特渐渐失去了对动画的兴趣
By the 1950s, Walt was losing interest in animation


60
00:03:26.056 --> 00:03:28.388
更多地开始关注真人电影
and his attention turned to live-action films,


61
00:03:28.525 --> 00:03:29.992
新兴的电视媒体
the new medium of television,


62
00:03:30.126 --> 00:03:32.424
首座迪斯尼主题公园的建设
and building the first theme park, Disneyland,


63
00:03:32.562 --> 00:03:34.928
而且计划着未来都市的图景
and planning futuristic cities of tomorrow.


64
00:03:35.165 --> 00:03:38.692
目前为止, 我们佛罗里达计划最重要的部分
By far, the most important part of our Florida Project,


65
00:03:38.835 --> 00:03:42.100
也是迪斯尼世界的核心内容
in fact, the heart of everything we'll be doing in Disney World,


66
00:03:42.238 --> 00:03:47.369
将是我们的“明日世界实验原型”, 即“未来世界”
will be our Experimental Prototype City of Tomorrow, Epcot.


67
00:03:47.811 --> 00:03:49.403
沃特1966年去世
Walt died in 1966,


68
00:03:49.546 --> 00:03:52.982
但迪斯尼仍在为孩子们制作着天真烂漫的卡通片
but the studio still made sweet, harmless, animated comedies for kids,


69
00:03:53.116 --> 00:03:57.553
监制人是一群大师级动画制作人, 被称为“九长老”
supervised by his master animators, the Nine Old Men,


70
00:03:57.687 --> 00:04:01.453
出品人是沃特的女婿, 工作室头号人物罗恩•米勒
and produced by Walt's son-in-law, studio head Ron Miller.


71
00:04:02.092 --> 00:04:05.755
我是兰迪•卡特莱特, 这是罗恩•米勒
I'm Randy Cartwright and this is Ron Miller.


72
00:04:05.895 --> 00:04:07.021
兰迪, 你好啊, 很高兴见到你
Randy! How are you? Good to see you.


73
00:04:07.163 --> 00:04:10.758
这是兰迪, 电影开了个好头
This is Randy. Great way to start the film.


74
00:04:10.900 --> 00:04:14.199
- 这是… 你的第一支广告吗?  - 没错
- Is this a new--? Your first commercial? - Ha, ha. Yup.


75
00:04:14.337 --> 00:04:15.395
拍这个干嘛?
What is this for?


76
00:04:15.538 --> 00:04:17.301
- 家庭电影而已 - 纪录片
- Just home movie. - It's a documentary.


77
00:04:17.440 --> 00:04:20.671
关于工作室的纪录片
Documentary of the animation studio.


78
00:04:20.810 --> 00:04:22.505
妈妈, 你好
Hi, Mom.


79
00:04:25.448 --> 00:04:27.143
很好, 开了个好头
Well, we're off to a good start.


80
00:04:27.283 --> 00:04:30.719
现在是1980年4月9日
Here it is, April 9th, 1980.


81
00:04:30.854 --> 00:04:33.789
我们要去采访大家了
This is the past to all you folks out there.


82
00:04:33.923 --> 00:04:38.326
我们马上进去, 看看大家在干嘛, 跟我来
And we're gonna go inside and see what it's like. Come on.


83
00:04:38.461 --> 00:04:40.827
不知为何, 迪斯尼公司大楼的走道里
For some reason, the halls of the Disney Animation building


84
00:04:40.964 --> 00:04:44.559
总是弥漫着冷却器, 铅笔屑和旧油毡的味道
always smelled faintly of swamp coolers and pencil shavings and old linoleum.


85
00:04:44.701 --> 00:04:46.760
这就是臭名昭著的老鼠窝
This is the infamous Rat's Nest.


86
00:04:46.903 --> 00:04:50.134
动画长期以来都是在这样的地方制作
Animation had been in this slow downward spiral for a long time,


87
00:04:50.273 --> 00:04:52.138
沃特在世时就一直这样
even since Walt Disney was alive.


88
00:04:52.275 --> 00:04:56.659
老一辈退休后, 加州艺术学院的年轻毕业生
As veteran animators retired, new kids, mostly from the Disney-sponsored school,


89
00:04:56.660 --> 00:04:57.879
开始挑起工作室大梁
CalArts, filled the hallways.


90
00:04:58.014 --> 00:05:00.175
鲁本, 你也是加艺毕业的吧
Why, Ruben, you're from CalArts also.


91
00:05:00.316 --> 00:05:01.908
没错, 你是哪位?
Right. And who are you?


92
00:05:02.051 --> 00:05:03.143
- 我? - 没错
- Me? - Yes.


93
00:05:03.286 --> 00:05:04.344
我是约翰•雷斯特
I'm John Lasseter.


94
00:05:04.487 --> 00:05:06.512
他是个摄像的, 马上就会走
He's the cameraman. He's leaving in a little while.


95
00:05:06.656 --> 00:05:08.556
要看看我的动画吗?
Could I show you animation?


96
00:05:08.691 --> 00:05:11.023
- 要看看我的动画吗? - 这就是动画
- Could I show you animation? - This is animation.


97
00:05:11.161 --> 00:05:12.924
我翻些东西给你看
Could I flip something for you?


98
00:05:13.062 --> 00:05:15.963
就是这个, 看好了, 彼得•潘
This is it. Look at that. Peter Pan.


99
00:05:16.099 --> 00:05:18.693
看着…
Oh, looks up and...


100
00:05:18.835 --> 00:05:21.201
这比我们今天做的还精彩
It's better than the magic we're making today,


101
00:05:21.337 --> 00:05:23.532
但我们也做不了什么
but we can't help that.


102
00:05:26.342 --> 00:05:30.608
我们是一群精力过剩, 需要发泄的人
We were full of a lot of pent-up youthful creative energy that had to go somewhere,


103
00:05:30.747 --> 00:05:35.184
而发泄渠道通常是: 长时间的午餐, 排球
so it was channeled into things like long lunches, volleyball games,


104
00:05:35.518 --> 00:05:37.213
年度讽刺漫画展
the annual caricature show,


105
00:05:37.353 --> 00:05:39.145
以及我最爱的
and my perennial favorite,


106
00:05:39.146 --> 00:05:42.954
艾迪•费舍和桃乐思•黛的假日秀
the holiday show that starred Eddie Fisher and Doris Day, for some unknown reason.


107
00:05:46.296 --> 00:05:50.027
这是我们的动画师罗恩•克莱门茨
This is one of our animators here. This is Ron Clements.


108
00:05:50.166 --> 00:05:53.602
他正在制作狐狸与猎狗中关于寡妇的场景
He's working on a scene of the Widow from The Fox and the Hound.


109
00:05:53.736 --> 00:05:58.173
- 不可思议, 这位是约翰•马斯克 - 谢谢, 谢谢
- Magically, here is Mr. John-ald Musker. - Thank you, thank you.


110
00:05:58.308 --> 00:06:00.902
他也是我们工作室的动画师
Another animator here at the magic factory.


111
00:06:01.377 --> 00:06:02.605
这是格兰•基恩
This is Glen Keane.


112
00:06:02.745 --> 00:06:04.042
他是一名指导动画师
He is a directing animator.


113
00:06:04.180 --> 00:06:07.479
我早上8点就来了
I've been here since 8:00 this morning.


114
00:06:08.151 --> 00:06:10.312
嘿, 蒂姆, 这是蒂姆•伯顿
Hi, Tim. This is Tim Burton,


115
00:06:10.453 --> 00:06:12.114
也是我们的同事
another one of our people here.


116
00:06:12.255 --> 00:06:15.053
罗恩•米勒清楚动画师的职业生涯不长
Ron Miller knew that Walt's guys were retiring fast.


117
00:06:15.191 --> 00:06:16.945
所以他必须不断启用新人
He had to raise a new crop of animators,


118
00:06:16.946 --> 00:06:18.217
同时也必须小心谨慎
but he was cautious about it.


119
00:06:18.361 --> 00:06:19.658
五年前的一件事令他大为光火
He got burned five years earlier


120
00:06:19.796 --> 00:06:23.630
当时他满怀信任地把动画部交给唐•布鲁斯主管
when he entrusted a charismatic animator named Don Bluth to lead the department.


121
00:06:23.766 --> 00:06:25.927
但布鲁斯这个人争议很大
But Bluth polarized the animators.


122
00:06:26.069 --> 00:06:29.505
崇拜者奉他为行业救世主
Some adored him as the messiah of animation and others...


123
00:06:29.639 --> 00:06:33.131
反对者则视其为自大狂
Well, others thought he was just another Walt wannabe.


124
00:06:33.776 --> 00:06:37.809
讽刺的是, 布鲁斯自己也对公司动画部失去了信心
lronically, Bluth himself became disillusioned with the studio's Animation Department.


125
00:06:37.947 --> 00:06:40.711
所以, 他在1979年生日时, 选择了辞职
So on his birthday in 1979, he resigned


126
00:06:40.850 --> 00:06:44.445
而且, 他带走了一半的动画师, 另立门户
and took half the animators with him to start his own studio.


127
00:06:44.954 --> 00:06:48.822
这场变故让狐狸与猎狗延期半年完成
The bombshell set back the release of The Fox and the Hound by six months


128
00:06:48.958 --> 00:06:52.155
米勒和整个工作室就这样惨遭背叛
and left Miller and the studio betrayed.


129
00:06:52.295 --> 00:06:54.763
当时迪斯尼存在着有趣的隔代现象
It was this interesting cross-generational thing


130
00:06:54.898 --> 00:06:58.800
一边是老一辈的传奇动画师
where you still had a few of these legendary Disney artists


131
00:06:58.935 --> 00:07:01.904
他们年逾花甲, 即将退休
who were now in their sixties and approaching retirement


132
00:07:02.038 --> 00:07:05.132
另一边则是一群二十来岁的年轻人
and then a bunch of young people in their twenties


133
00:07:05.275 --> 00:07:10.144
他们对动画充满了简单真挚的激情与热爱
who were really, really excited and sort of passionate about this medium.


134
00:07:10.613 --> 00:07:14.014
前辈的悉心教导当然很好
It was thrilling to learn from the masters.


135
00:07:14.150 --> 00:07:15.694
但大家总觉得
But there was a feeling like


136
00:07:15.695 --> 00:07:18.177
我们可以做出更好的作品
that somehow we could be making better films.


137
00:07:18.321 --> 00:07:20.221
当时, 公司做了一份调查
Around that time, the studio did a survey


138
00:07:20.356 --> 00:07:23.325
发现很大部分青少年观影者
that revealed a majority of teenage moviegoers


139
00:07:23.459 --> 00:07:25.620
对迪斯尼影片表示厌恶
wouldn't be caught dead near a Disney movie.


140
00:07:25.762 --> 00:07:30.859
我们就这样等待, 希望变革来临
We were just waiting, waiting for something, anything to happen.


141
00:07:31.100 --> 00:07:33.432
周一, 我们报道了迪斯尼工作室
On Monday, we reported that Walt Disney Studios


142
00:07:33.569 --> 00:07:34.939
正面临财务困境
was on shaky financial ground,


143
00:07:34.940 --> 00:07:36.629
因为其表现乏力的电影业务
because of its troubled Film Division


144
00:07:36.773 --> 00:07:39.037
以及盈利不佳的未来世界项目
and weak earnings from the Epcot Center in Florida.


145
00:07:39.175 --> 00:07:42.076
然而, 之后事态发生了戏剧性的变化
However, since that report, there have been dramatic developments.


146
00:07:42.211 --> 00:07:45.476
短短的四日内, 迪斯尼股价飙升了16%
In just four days, Disney stock jumped 16 percent,


147
00:07:45.615 --> 00:07:47.845
达到每股58美元的高价
topping off at around $58 a share.


148
00:07:47.984 --> 00:07:50.077
分析人士为该事件给出两点解释
Analysts attribute the jump to two factors.


149
00:07:50.219 --> 00:07:53.086
美人鱼 - 一部融合曼哈顿与童话的青春喜剧片
Splash, the youth-oriented comedy about a mermaid in Manhattan,


150
00:07:53.222 --> 00:07:57.522
以上映三天600万的票房震惊了电影界
stunned Hollywood by racking up over $6 million in its opening three days.


151
00:07:57.660 --> 00:08:00.754
它成为了迪斯尼吸金最快的电影
That's the best opening for any movie in Disney's history.


152
00:08:00.897 --> 00:08:04.799
另一大意外, 是罗伊•迪斯尼辞去董事长职务
Another surprise, the resignation of Roy E. Disney as chairman of the board.


153
00:08:04.934 --> 00:08:06.923
他是沃特的侄子, 是沃特弟弟所生
He's Walt's nephew and son of Walt's brother,


154
00:08:06.924 --> 00:08:08.028
也是公司创始人之一
the company's co-founder.


155
00:08:08.171 --> 00:08:11.332
公司真正的业务中心, 曾经是
The real heartbeat of this company was,


156
00:08:11.333 --> 00:08:14.576
现在是, 将来也永远是电影
is and will always be the film business.


157
00:08:14.711 --> 00:08:17.737
因为电影是一切创意的源泉
Because from the film business comes the ideas


158
00:08:17.880 --> 00:08:22.340
这些创意可以应用到主题公园中
that then generate new things in the parks.


159
00:08:22.485 --> 00:08:24.112
可以推动新的营销, 新的…
New promotions, new--


160
00:08:24.253 --> 00:08:29.190
总之就是公司保持新鲜生命的源动力
A kind of a sense of continuing newness about the company in general.


161
00:08:29.325 --> 00:08:32.089
当我们电影做得不好时
And when that began to fail--


162
00:08:32.228 --> 00:08:35.082
我们就会开始渐渐
And I actually, somewhere along the line,


163
00:08:35.083 --> 00:08:36.892
听到流言蜚语
began hearing things like,


164
00:08:37.033 --> 00:08:39.797
“我看, 他们根本就无心做电影了,
"Well, I don't think they really wanna stay in the movie business,


165
00:08:39.936 --> 00:08:43.702
拍得总是马马虎虎, 我们也根本不想看了
because it's not doing very well and we don't really even need it anyway."


166
00:08:43.840 --> 00:08:48.539
这些话令我很苦恼, 因为我…
And that gave me all sorts of problems, because I, you know--


167
00:08:48.678 --> 00:08:50.051
我记得有人说
I remember saying at one point,


168
00:08:50.052 --> 00:08:51.647
“如果你真那么想,
"Well, if you really think that way,


169
00:08:51.781 --> 00:08:53.646
那你就真的离电影太远了。”
then what you're doing is running a museum."


170
00:08:54.350 --> 00:08:56.784
人们嘲讽罗伊为“沃特的笨侄子”
People always talked about Roy as the idiot nephew.


171
00:08:56.919 --> 00:08:58.216
“笨侄子”成了他的绰号
That was his nickname.


172
00:08:58.354 --> 00:09:00.584
而事实并非如此
Nothing could be really further from the truth.


173
00:09:00.723 --> 00:09:03.715
他聪明, 谦逊且雷厉风行
He was smart, unassuming and powerful.


174
00:09:03.860 --> 00:09:05.762
你很容易低估他
You could easily underestimate him,


175
00:09:05.763 --> 00:09:07.557
但低估他是很危险的
but you did so at your own peril.


176
00:09:08.331 --> 00:09:09.437
1984年
In 1984,


177
00:09:09.438 --> 00:09:12.597
专做蓄意收购的索尔•斯坦伯格盯上了迪斯尼
the corporate raider Saul Steinberg turned his sights on Disney.


178
00:09:12.735 --> 00:09:14.334
他扬言要买下整家公司
He threatened to buy the company,


179
00:09:14.335 --> 00:09:16.466
然后分拆出售获利
break it up and sell the parts for a profit.


180
00:09:16.606 --> 00:09:18.484
作为回应, 迪斯尼董事会决定
The board countered by paying


181
00:09:18.485 --> 00:09:21.270
高价回购斯坦伯格所持股票
Steinberg a premium to buy back his shares.


182
00:09:21.411 --> 00:09:22.935
迪斯尼被耍了
It was greenmail.


183
00:09:24.647 --> 00:09:26.945
多年后, 罗伊和他表弟罗恩•米勒
For years, Roy and his cousin-in-law, Ron Miller,


184
00:09:27.083 --> 00:09:28.710
在董事局会议上相向而坐
sat across the boardroom table.


185
00:09:28.851 --> 00:09:30.478
他们为一件事争执不下
And now the two were at odds with


186
00:09:30.620 --> 00:09:33.384
那就是董事会当年对威胁收购的处理
how the board was handling the takeover threat.


187
00:09:33.523 --> 00:09:34.859
会议最后得出结论
And we finally came to the conclusion


188
00:09:34.860 --> 00:09:37.482
我们身在局内, 别无选择
that we can't do anything on the inside,


189
00:09:37.627 --> 00:09:41.529
虽然我反对, 但毕竟孤掌难鸣
because I'm the lone voice of dissent on this board.


190
00:09:41.664 --> 00:09:45.725
所以我选择向董事会请辞
So I resigned from the board of directors.


191
00:09:45.868 --> 00:09:48.530
我的辞呈引起了很多关注
And it got enormous amounts of attention.


192
00:09:48.671 --> 00:09:52.698
第二天早上, 我收到了
I had a stack the next morning of phone messages


193
00:09:52.842 --> 00:09:55.140
无数的电话留言
that probably was three, four inches deep.


194
00:09:55.278 --> 00:09:58.577
其中一条来自迈克尔•埃斯纳
One of the messages in that stack was Eisner.


195
00:09:58.714 --> 00:10:01.282
他差不多在事件发生一年多前加入董事会
And I had known Michael because he'd come maybe a


196
00:10:01.283 --> 00:10:03.277
那之前, 我就在艺术学院里认识他了
year before that on to the board at CalArts.


197
00:10:03.419 --> 00:10:05.944
迈克尔不是商科出身, 他是英语专业的
Michael wasn't an M.B.A. He was an English major.


198
00:10:06.089 --> 00:10:07.147
他在纽约长大
He grew up in New York,


199
00:10:07.290 --> 00:10:08.401
早年的工作
where one of his first jobs


200
00:10:08.402 --> 00:10:10.726
是为电视台制作儿童节目
was programming kids' television for ABC.


201
00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:13.727
他在派拉蒙工作期间取得过骄人的业绩
And Michael had an amazing track record coming from Paramount.


202
00:10:13.863 --> 00:10:17.822
参与过奥斯卡获奖影片《母女情深》的制作
He'd had hits, Oscar nominations, Terms of Endearment.


203
00:10:17.967 --> 00:10:22.063
他接手迪斯尼时, 正春风得意
He was a winner when he was hired to come in and run Disney.


204
00:10:22.772 --> 00:10:26.230
但他有时也会把事情搞砸
He also was a man who liked to blow things up.


205
00:10:26.375 --> 00:10:27.786
是弗兰克•威尔斯建议罗伊
It was Frank Wells that gave


206
00:10:27.787 --> 00:10:30.004
让迈克尔担任董事局主席
Roy the idea of making Michael the chairman.


207
00:10:30.146 --> 00:10:31.050
弗兰克与罗伊
Frank and Roy were


208
00:10:31.051 --> 00:10:33.411
早年在波莫纳大学是同班同学
classmates at Pomona College in the early '50s.


209
00:10:34.383 --> 00:10:37.819
我觉得弗兰克更像个精明的商人
I thought, you know, Frank's more of a businessman


210
00:10:37.954 --> 00:10:39.819
迈克尔则学究气重些
and Michael is a little nuts.


211
00:10:39.956 --> 00:10:41.975
他们两人的组合
And the two together kind of


212
00:10:41.976 --> 00:10:45.292
让我想起沃特和我父亲
in some ways made me think of Walt and my dad.


213
00:10:45.428 --> 00:10:49.489
于是我们想知道, “你们二人打算怎么做?”
So we began saying, "How would you two like to take this job?"


214
00:10:49.632 --> 00:10:52.692
迪斯尼王国管理层进行了变动重组
There's been a management shake-up in the Magic Kingdom of Disney.


215
00:10:52.835 --> 00:10:55.303
两位好莱坞高管被举荐
Two Hollywood studio executives have been chosen


216
00:10:55.438 --> 00:10:57.133
掌管迪斯尼公司
to run Walt Disney Productions,


217
00:10:57.273 --> 00:11:00.140
这是迪斯尼第一次由外人担任最高层
the first time outsiders have been brought in at the top.


218
00:11:00.276 --> 00:11:04.511
迪斯尼董事会推选来自派拉蒙的迈克尔•埃斯纳为主席
The Disney board of directors chose Michael Eisner of Paramount Pictures as chairman,


219
00:11:04.647 --> 00:11:07.639
以及华纳兄弟的弗兰克•威尔斯为首席运营官
and Frank Wells of Warner Bros. As chief operating officer.


220
00:11:08.151 --> 00:11:10.881
新晋管理层的第一要务
The first goal, really, of new management


221
00:11:11.020 --> 00:11:15.287
就是认真地重振电影业务
is gonna be getting back in the movie business in a very serious way,


222
00:11:15.424 --> 00:11:17.358
不能马马虎虎, 拍完了事
in the sense of not only just making movies,


223
00:11:17.493 --> 00:11:19.324
要有新的想法和创意
but coming up with new ideas.


224
00:11:19.795 --> 00:11:22.195
二人的组合确实让公司变得与众不同
Their partnership really made the company special.


225
00:11:22.331 --> 00:11:24.856
人们看来, 迈克尔行事鲁莽
There was this perception that Michael was a shoot-from-the-hip,


226
00:11:25.001 --> 00:11:26.229
为人不拘小节
back-of-the-napkin kind of guy,


227
00:11:26.369 --> 00:11:29.167
弗兰克则工整细致, 井井有条
and Frank was very organized and ran things in an orderly manner.


228
00:11:29.872 --> 00:11:31.546
但很多时候, 事实恰恰相反
But in many ways, it was the opposite.


229
00:11:31.547 --> 00:11:33.000
迈克尔更为正常理性
Michael was kind of the sane one.


230
00:11:33.142 --> 00:11:35.337
而弗兰克常做些出格疯狂的事
And Frank, he did bold and crazy things,


231
00:11:35.478 --> 00:11:38.140
比如横渡海洋, 攀登世界各大著名山峰
like swimming oceans, climbing the great summits of the world


232
00:11:38.281 --> 00:11:41.682
甚至于半夜三点打电话问人高飞的本名
and calling at 3 a.M. To ask what Goofy's original name was.


233
00:11:41.817 --> 00:11:45.583
我们欢迎迪斯尼的登山勇士, 弗兰克•威尔斯
Please welcome my mountain-climbing Disney teammate, Frank Wells.


234
00:11:45.721 --> 00:11:48.155
这次员工论坛让我明白
I figured out from this employee forum what the difference is


235
00:11:48.291 --> 00:11:50.657
首席执行官(CEO)与首席运营官(COO)的区别
between chief operating officer and chief executive officer.


236
00:11:50.793 --> 00:11:53.353
COO负责完成一些危险动作
Chief operating officer is in charge of doing dangerous things,


237
00:11:53.496 --> 00:11:56.056
比如说我就要吊在钢丝上跟小叮当一起飞
like when I have to fly here with Tinker Bell on a tiny wire.


238
00:11:56.199 --> 00:11:58.667
CEO, 则负责搞笑
Chief executive officer, he's in charge of funny.


239
00:11:58.801 --> 00:11:59.995
弗兰克?
Frank?


240
00:12:00.136 --> 00:12:01.831
嘿, 迈克尔
Hi, Michael.


241
00:12:06.776 --> 00:12:09.745
1984年我回到公司
I came back to the company in 1984


242
00:12:09.879 --> 00:12:13.178
有些漫不经心地对迈克尔说
and, rather cavalier way at the time, said to Michael,


243
00:12:13.316 --> 00:12:15.477
“为何不让我来掌管动画部
"Why don't you let me have the Animation Department,


244
00:12:15.618 --> 00:12:17.408
因为我现在是很珍贵的
because I may be the only guy right now,


245
00:12:17.409 --> 00:12:19.019
新人们不断加入以后
with all these new people coming in,


246
00:12:19.155 --> 00:12:22.522
熟悉整个流程, 又认识大部分人的, 恐怕只有我了
who at least understands the process and knows most of the people."


247
00:12:22.658 --> 00:12:25.422
当时的制作工艺正逐渐被淘汰
The state of the art at that moment was kind of waning


248
00:12:25.561 --> 00:12:30.089
工作室对老式工艺也不是特别依赖
and the enthusiasm of the studio itself towards it had not been real strong.


249
00:12:30.233 --> 00:12:32.724
所以我有些关心这个问题
So I just felt a little protective about it.


250
00:12:33.402 --> 00:12:36.394
我来到约翰•马斯克的办公室
And I was in John Musker's office.


251
00:12:36.539 --> 00:12:38.063
记得之后史蒂夫•休利特走进来
And I think it was Steve Hulett came in


252
00:12:38.207 --> 00:12:41.267
告诉我们罗恩•米勒辞职了
with the memo saying that Ron Miller had resigned.


253
00:12:41.410 --> 00:12:45.278
我们都很震惊, 一时难以接受
And we were shocked and it was a huge bombshell to go off.


254
00:12:45.414 --> 00:12:47.211
但我心里明白, 这是个大好消息
But I thought it was, you know, terrific news,


255
00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:48.625
这可能意味着
that maybe it meant that things


256
00:12:48.626 --> 00:12:50.478
工作室要往好的方向发展
were gonna actually get better at the studio.


257
00:12:50.620 --> 00:12:52.356
约翰应该跟我想的一样
And John, I think, felt the same way.


258
00:12:52.357 --> 00:12:53.953
他看起来非常高兴
He seemed pretty excited about it.


259
00:12:54.090 --> 00:12:57.856
而罗恩则有些忧伤地说
But Ron was worried, in a sort of melancholy mood, said,


260
00:12:57.994 --> 00:12:59.791
“永远不要高兴得太早”
"It could always get worse."


261
00:12:59.929 --> 00:13:01.556
这是一次来自好莱坞的入侵
It was an invasion from Hollywood.


262
00:13:01.697 --> 00:13:04.325
停车场排满了宝马和保时捷
The parking lot was jammed with BMWs and Porsches.


263
00:13:04.467 --> 00:13:06.958
我记得装修工拆的那些墙
And I remember interior decorators tearing down walls


264
00:13:07.103 --> 00:13:09.663
是1939年后, 就不曾变过的
that hadn't been touched since 1939.


265
00:13:09.805 --> 00:13:13.002
全新的贝伯地毯取代了使用多年的油毡
New Berber carpeting replaced decades-old linoleum.


266
00:13:13.142 --> 00:13:15.110
我不知道油毡有什么不好的
I couldn't figure out what's wrong with linoleum.


267
00:13:15.244 --> 00:13:17.303
要知道, 沃特•迪斯尼当年就走在那油毡上
I mean, Walt Disney walked on that linoleum.


268
00:13:17.446 --> 00:13:19.778
甚至连零食贩卖机也被拆了
Even the snack machines were being torn out.


269
00:13:19.915 --> 00:13:21.849
再见, 售货机
Goodbye, vending machines.


270
00:13:21.984 --> 00:13:24.748
当时, 我还不擅长跟好莱坞打交道
I had no experience with Hollywood at that time.


271
00:13:24.887 --> 00:13:29.449
之前跟我打交道的都是和蔼的老一辈
My experience was with kindly old men with cardigan sweaters.


272
00:13:29.592 --> 00:13:32.322
他们通常心平气和, 慈眉善目
And they would sit around and pat you on the back.


273
00:13:32.461 --> 00:13:34.393
现在的这帮家伙
And here's these guys hollering


274
00:13:34.394 --> 00:13:37.262
则是口无遮拦, 脏话连篇
foul language in the middle of story meetings.


275
00:13:37.400 --> 00:13:40.062
这像一泼冷水, 突然把我惊醒
And a splash of cold water, suddenly a wake-up to reality.


276
00:13:40.202 --> 00:13:42.295
把我带回现实
You're in the real world here.


277
00:13:42.972 --> 00:13:44.405
大家好, 我是迈克尔•埃斯纳
Hello. I'm Michael Eisner.


278
00:13:44.540 --> 00:13:46.531
欢迎来到迪斯尼周日电影秀
And welcome to The Disney Sunday Movie.


279
00:13:46.676 --> 00:13:50.407
迈克尔•埃斯纳是迪斯尼那一批人中
Michael Eisner is the irreverent kid from the Disney generation


280
00:13:50.546 --> 00:13:52.514
最不守规矩的
who has taken over the toy store.


281
00:13:52.982 --> 00:13:55.382
迪斯尼也让他变得家财万贯
The money alone is right out of Fantasyland.


282
00:13:55.518 --> 00:13:59.784
他的薪酬和股份价值千万美元
His salary and stock options are worth tens of millions of dollars.


283
00:13:59.922 --> 00:14:02.152
在迪斯尼周日电影秀中
He may look every inch the company chairman


284
00:14:02.291 --> 00:14:05.419
他可能看起来一本正经
when he is taping the introduction to The Disney Sunday Night Movie.


285
00:14:05.561 --> 00:14:09.622
但实际上, 他是所有人中玩得最开心的
But in fact, he's having more fun than any other boy on the block.


286
00:14:09.765 --> 00:14:11.665
瞧, 米奇, 我们的朋友也来了
Look, Mickey. Some of our friends are coming.


287
00:14:11.801 --> 00:14:13.098
嘿, 米妮
Hey, Minnie.


288
00:14:13.235 --> 00:14:15.430
迈克尔上任CEO后的第一步
So one of the first things that Michael did as CEO


289
00:14:15.571 --> 00:14:18.301
就是将他派拉蒙的旧部杰弗里•卡岑伯格招入麾下
was to bring in Jeffrey Katzenberg, his colleague from Paramount,


290
00:14:18.441 --> 00:14:21.103
让他掌管迪斯尼的电影部
to run the Film Division of Disney.


291
00:14:21.243 --> 00:14:23.177
杰弗里早年在纽约从政
Jeffrey got his start in New York politics,


292
00:14:23.312 --> 00:14:25.712
担任市长约翰•林赛的幕僚
working in the office of Mayor John Lindsay,


293
00:14:25.848 --> 00:14:29.409
当时大家给他的绰号是“狂小子”
where his affectionate nickname was Squirt.


294
00:14:30.086 --> 00:14:31.144
在派拉蒙电影公司
At Paramount Pictures,


295
00:14:31.287 --> 00:14:34.085
他在迪勒和埃斯纳的阴影下发展
he studied in the shadow of Barry Diller and Michael Eisner.


296
00:14:34.223 --> 00:14:38.023
在那里, 人们给他的外号是“金毛猎犬”
And there his nickname was the Golden Retriever.


297
00:14:38.160 --> 00:14:39.650
在迪斯尼, 他不再有绰号了
At Disney, he really had no nickname,


298
00:14:39.795 --> 00:14:42.696
因为在这里, 他这可以走出他人的阴影
because this was the place where he could step out of the shadows


299
00:14:42.832 --> 00:14:44.493
在好莱坞闯出自己的事业
and make his mark on Hollywood.


300
00:14:44.633 --> 00:14:45.998
在派拉蒙时, 我就注意到他了
I sought him out at Paramount.


301
00:14:46.135 --> 00:14:48.467
共事过程中, 我发现他优秀极了
We'd worked together. He was just fantastic.


302
00:14:48.604 --> 00:14:51.596
他很勤奋, 有担当, 有所执迷
He was a worker. He was committed. He was obsessed.


303
00:14:51.741 --> 00:14:53.231
他擅长交际
He made relationships.


304
00:14:53.376 --> 00:14:56.777
一旦我们发现优秀的人才, 他就会设法进行拉拢
If we found somebody good, he would lasso him into our company.


305
00:14:56.912 --> 00:14:57.943
他在派拉蒙这么做
He did it at Paramount


306
00:14:57.944 --> 00:15:00.006
在迪斯尼也是, 而且做得很好
and he did it at Disney and he did it great.


307
00:15:00.149 --> 00:15:04.711
我一直记得来到迪斯尼的第一天
So I always remember my first day at Disney when I showed up


308
00:15:04.854 --> 00:15:07.118
我走进迈克尔的办公室, 他说
and I went to Michael's office and he said,


309
00:15:07.256 --> 00:15:08.814
“过来, 我给你看点东西”
"Come here, I wanna show you something."


310
00:15:08.958 --> 00:15:11.722
我走过去, 他正看着窗外
And I walked over and he was looking out his window.


311
00:15:11.861 --> 00:15:13.453
从他站的位置
And, you know, from his corner,


312
00:15:13.596 --> 00:15:16.861
他指向窗外的七彩大楼
he pointed down to the Ink and Paint building.


313
00:15:16.999 --> 00:15:18.933
问道 你知道他们在里面做什么吗
He said, "Do you know what they do down there?"


314
00:15:19.068 --> 00:15:20.126
我说 不知道
And I said,"No."


315
00:15:20.269 --> 00:15:22.464
他说 那是他们制作动画电影的地方
He said,"That's where they make the animated movies."


316
00:15:22.605 --> 00:15:23.949
我说 是吗? 他答道 是的
I went,"Really?" He said,"Yes."


317
00:15:23.950 --> 00:15:25.597
他又说 现在这归你管了
And he said,"And that's your problem."


318
00:15:26.609 --> 00:15:29.874
第一次意见分歧发生在一部备受瞩目的电影上
The first culture clash happened on a much-anticipated film


319
00:15:30.012 --> 00:15:32.503
这部电影制作期长, 投资巨大
that was years in the making and millions over budget,


320
00:15:32.648 --> 00:15:33.706
片名为: 黑神锅传奇
The Black Cauldron.


321
00:15:33.849 --> 00:15:35.817
他不知所措, 他上窜下跳
He's overwhelmed. He'd be jumping up and down.


322
00:15:37.653 --> 00:15:41.180
年轻组员很不耐烦, 急于展现他们的点子
The younger guys were really impatient and anxious to show what they could do,


323
00:15:41.323 --> 00:15:44.625
他们觉得保守的老一辈拖了后腿
but they felt like they were being held back by the remnants of the old guard.


324
00:15:45.161 --> 00:15:46.376
而年长的组员则认为
While the older guys thought


325
00:15:46.377 --> 00:15:48.460
这帮小子乳臭未干, 应该安分点
the kids were brats and should get back to work.


326
00:15:48.597 --> 00:15:52.863
黑神锅传奇这部电影, 我们从五本书开始
In the case of The Black Cauldron, we started with five books


327
00:15:53.002 --> 00:15:54.765
把它们浓缩到一本
and had to condense them down into one.


328
00:15:54.904 --> 00:15:57.099
我到岗后的前几个星期
In the first couple of weeks I was at the studio,


329
00:15:57.239 --> 00:15:59.639
观看了黑神锅传奇
I saw The Black Cauldron.


330
00:15:59.775 --> 00:16:03.336
这是部黑暗而棘手的片子
It was a very dark movie and a very troubled movie.


331
00:16:03.479 --> 00:16:07.813
实在是太, 太, 太暴力恐怖了
"This is just way, way, way too violent and too scary.


332
00:16:07.950 --> 00:16:10.578
必须要做一些删减
You have to edit some of these things out."


333
00:16:10.719 --> 00:16:12.812
他们说, 你不能删减动画电影
They said, "Well, you can't edit an animated movie."


334
00:16:12.955 --> 00:16:16.083
我说, 当然可以。而他们说, 不, 不可以的
I said,"Well, of course you can." And they said,"No, you can't."


335
00:16:16.225 --> 00:16:17.522
嘿, 不行, 别这样
Hey. No, you don't.


336
00:16:17.660 --> 00:16:20.757
可能你会觉得我在挑起内部矛盾
Honestly, you would think that I was causing World War Three at the studio,


337
00:16:20.896 --> 00:16:24.764
因为我确实说过, 你们把片子送到剪辑室
because I literally said,"Well, you get the film and bring it to an edit bay


338
00:16:24.900 --> 00:16:27.095
我来教你们如何删减动画片
and I'm gonna show you how you edit an animated movie."


339
00:16:27.236 --> 00:16:28.294
我认真的
I mean it.


340
00:16:29.171 --> 00:16:32.334
杰弗里亲力亲为, 强硬霸道
Jeffrey was hands-on, elbows-on, sharp elbows-on.


341
00:16:32.475 --> 00:16:35.205
你永远猜不透他的喜怒
You never knew if he was gonna hug you or kick you.


342
00:16:35.344 --> 00:16:37.583
一次接受采访时, 他说道
He said in an interview around that time,


343
00:16:37.584 --> 00:16:39.713
我们要唤醒睡美人
"We've got to wake up Sleeping Beauty."


344
00:16:39.849 --> 00:16:42.409
黑魔神的制片人乔•黑尔听后很生气
Then Joe Hale, the producer of The Black Cauldron, was furious.


345
00:16:42.551 --> 00:16:46.214
他们以为自己是谁?他说, 睡美人明明已经醒了
"Who are these guys?"He said. "Sleeping Beauty is awake."


346
00:16:46.355 --> 00:16:48.789
不久后, 他被炒了
He was fired not long after.


347
00:16:48.924 --> 00:16:51.484
黑魔神耗资4400万美元
Black Cauldron cost $44 million to make


348
00:16:51.627 --> 00:16:53.857
票房收入却只及投资一半
and made less than half that at the box office.


349
00:16:53.996 --> 00:16:56.464
更加耻辱和伤人的是
And, to add insult to injury,


350
00:16:56.599 --> 00:16:59.727
它的票房还不如爱心熊的电影
it was beat out at the box office by The Care Bears Movie.


351
00:17:01.770 --> 00:17:04.967
那一刻, 迪斯尼动画发展跌入谷底
That day, Disney Animation hit bottom.


352
00:17:05.107 --> 00:17:07.473
又见到罗恩•克莱门茨了
This is Ron Clements again.


353
00:17:07.610 --> 00:17:10.272
讲讲贝克街的巴兹尔这部电影吧
Explain a little bit about Basil of Baker Street.


354
00:17:10.412 --> 00:17:14.815
这部电影讲了一只老鼠的故事
Well, Basil of Baker Street is about a little mouse


355
00:17:14.950 --> 00:17:17.282
他有点像福尔摩斯
that is just like Sherlock Holmes.


356
00:17:17.419 --> 00:17:20.547
刚开始罗伊给我们安排了一项任务
One of the first things Roy did was he arranged one day


357
00:17:20.689 --> 00:17:25.319
就是浏览整个电影的故事板
for us to be pitched the storyboards for the entire movie.


358
00:17:25.461 --> 00:17:29.261
好像动画片就应该这么做
It's like going back to what animation really is supposed to be.


359
00:17:29.398 --> 00:17:32.458
那三个小时时间里
And for the better part of three hours,


360
00:17:32.601 --> 00:17:37.868
我们一张张看完了整部电影的故事板
literally the entire movie was pitched to us.


361
00:17:38.007 --> 00:17:40.134
你看完一张, 接着看下一张
You go through one storyboard, then they bring another


362
00:17:40.276 --> 00:17:41.800
坐在那好几个小时
and you'd sit there for hours and--


363
00:17:41.944 --> 00:17:45.937
我都不记得第一张故事板的内容
I couldn't remember what was in the first storyboard.


364
00:17:46.081 --> 00:17:47.946
这对我来说有些困难
It was a very hard process for me to deal with.


365
00:17:48.083 --> 00:17:50.051
因为我主要负责的是剧本方面
I'd been used to dealing in the script area.


366
00:17:50.185 --> 00:17:52.050
我们看完后, 都如释重负, 说道
So when it was over, we all sort of said,


367
00:17:52.187 --> 00:17:54.052
非常感谢, 做得好
"Thanks very much," And,"Great job."


368
00:17:54.189 --> 00:17:56.521
迈克尔说, 跟我一起回办公室
And Michael said, "Walk back to my office with me."


369
00:17:56.659 --> 00:17:58.593
我们往回, 走到办公室
So we walked back. On the way back to the office,


370
00:17:58.727 --> 00:18:00.957
他问, 你觉得怎么样?我说, 不知道
he said,"What do you think?" I said,"L have no idea."


371
00:18:02.631 --> 00:18:04.098
他说, 我也是
And he said,"Neither do I."


372
00:18:04.233 --> 00:18:06.098
我说, 这样吧
I said,"Well, here's the thing.


373
00:18:06.235 --> 00:18:07.444
我们有175名员工
We have 175 people and


374
00:18:07.445 --> 00:18:09.864
我们每天付给他们工钱
we're paying them every day to come to work.


375
00:18:10.005 --> 00:18:11.744
工资反正是要发的
And we're gonna pay them


376
00:18:11.745 --> 00:18:13.657
无论他们做不做这片子
whether they make this movie or they don't make this movie,


377
00:18:13.658 --> 00:18:15.604
所以我们还是做比较好
so I guess we probably ought to make the movie."


378
00:18:15.744 --> 00:18:18.474
然后他说, 我也是这么想的
And he says to me, "Well, that's exactly my feeling too."


379
00:18:18.614 --> 00:18:21.208
真人电影发展很快, 杰弗里需要更多办公场地
The live-action business was booming and Jeffrey needed offices


380
00:18:21.350 --> 00:18:22.839
给他的新晋明星
for his new stable of stars,


381
00:18:22.840 --> 00:18:24.808
比如贝蒂•米德勒和罗宾•威廉姆斯
like Bette Midler and Robin Williams.


382
00:18:25.187 --> 00:18:27.485
他决定占用动画部的办公楼
He wanted the animation building.


383
00:18:27.623 --> 00:18:29.921
消息从动画部头儿罗伊•迪斯尼处传下来
The news came down from the head of animation, Roy Disney,


384
00:18:30.059 --> 00:18:31.686
他通知动画部的员工
announcing that the animators would have


385
00:18:31.827 --> 00:18:33.727
必须搬出该办公楼
to move out of the building and off the lot.


386
00:18:34.029 --> 00:18:35.394
这到底怎么回事?
What was going on here? I mean,


387
00:18:35.531 --> 00:18:36.625
要知道这栋楼
this was the building where


388
00:18:36.626 --> 00:18:38.329
可是沃特•迪斯尼制作灰姑娘和小飞侠的地方
Walt Disney made Cinderella and Peter Pan,


389
00:18:38.467 --> 00:18:39.900
就这样腾出来给别人?
and we were having to vacate?


390
00:18:40.035 --> 00:18:41.400
整个决定只能参考一份备忘录
All there was was this memo.


391
00:18:41.537 --> 00:18:43.732
没有会议, 没有辩论, 只有一份备忘录
There was no meeting, no debate, just a memo.


392
00:18:43.973 --> 00:18:46.305
貌似罗伊也不想做过多解释
I guess Roy didn't want the confrontation.


393
00:18:46.442 --> 00:18:49.070
离开那天, 两百名不安的员工
On our last day, 200 frightened people,


394
00:18:49.211 --> 00:18:52.180
昔日辉煌的迪斯尼动画工作室的残兵剩将
the remnants of Disney's once great Animation Studio,


395
00:18:52.314 --> 00:18:54.509
聚集在老动画部大楼前
gathered on the steps of the old Animation building


396
00:18:54.650 --> 00:18:57.983
留下最后一张合影
for one last photo before we left.


397
00:18:58.754 --> 00:19:01.348
之后我们搬到了新办公楼
So to carry that forward into the new building,


398
00:19:01.490 --> 00:19:04.118
坐落于格兰岱尔市, 选址马马虎虎
which was in Glendale, not a great area,


399
00:19:04.259 --> 00:19:08.093
建筑就基本上是一些简陋可怜的房子
but the building itself was such a gutted wretch of a building,


400
00:19:08.230 --> 00:19:09.652
用空心砖砌起来
with just cinder block


401
00:19:09.653 --> 00:19:12.496
铺着破烂的地毯, 外围有铁丝网
and torn-up carpet and barbed wire around it


402
00:19:12.635 --> 00:19:16.332
肮脏的小车库满是碎酒瓶子
and broken bottles on the crummy little parking lot.


403
00:19:16.472 --> 00:19:18.997
爱德, 这几天都在忙什么?
So, Ed, what are you doing nowadays?


404
00:19:19.141 --> 00:19:20.870
我就对着桌子发发呆
I'm just emotionally under my desk.


405
00:19:21.010 --> 00:19:23.638
我们都认定一周之内就要卷铺盖走人
Well, we were all pretty sure that we'd be fired in a week or so,


406
00:19:23.779 --> 00:19:26.771
所以决定为迪斯尼动画来一次特别的庆祝
so we decided to celebrate the apparent end of Disney Animation


407
00:19:26.915 --> 00:19:30.248
那就是全景再现电影现代启示录
with a full-scale reenactment of Apocalypse Now.


408
00:19:45.901 --> 00:19:48.802
我们没有长长的黑走廊了, 现在都是小隔间
We don't have long dark hallways anymore. We got cubicles.


409
00:19:48.937 --> 00:19:52.168
办公区采用了开放的设计, 你无处躲藏
The warehouse was an open plan, so you couldn't really hide.


410
00:19:52.307 --> 00:19:55.174
大家随时可以进行即兴的交流
It opened the place to frequent and spontaneous communications


411
00:19:55.310 --> 00:19:57.073
无论是在过道, 还是洗手间
in the hallways, in the men's room.


412
00:19:57.212 --> 00:19:58.270
来吧, 过来
Come on in. Come on.


413
00:19:58.414 --> 00:19:59.642
很多从此屏障被打破了
The barriers were down.


414
00:20:00.649 --> 00:20:03.174
搬迁后, 杰弗里召集全体动画师开会
After the move, Jeffrey called a meeting of all the animators,


415
00:20:03.318 --> 00:20:05.684
大家可以发问和表达意见
so the crew could air their questions and concerns.


416
00:20:05.821 --> 00:20:07.948
杰弗里站起来, 说: 拿出你们最尖锐的问题
So Jeffrey got up and said, "Give me your best shot.


417
00:20:08.090 --> 00:20:09.346
别给我留面子
Hit me in the solar plexus.


418
00:20:09.347 --> 00:20:11.116
随便问, 我脸皮厚得很
Ask me anything. I've got rhino skin."


419
00:20:11.260 --> 00:20:12.634
有人便问道
And somebody piped up and said,


420
00:20:12.635 --> 00:20:14.252
你简直不知道自己在做什么
"We don't think you know what you're doing."


421
00:20:14.396 --> 00:20:16.762
我回答到: 听着, 我就在这, 哪儿也不去
And I said, "Look, I'm here. I'm not going away.


422
00:20:16.899 --> 00:20:18.689
而且我很乐意
And I'm more than happy to


423
00:20:18.690 --> 00:20:21.927
与你们相处, 向你们学习
learn and take the time and be educated by you.


424
00:20:22.071 --> 00:20:25.802
但没办法, 我们最近的几部动画片
The fact is that the last couple of animated movies made


425
00:20:25.941 --> 00:20:27.533
都做得不尽如人意
were not particularly good."


426
00:20:27.676 --> 00:20:30.008
动画部会议开得很频繁
The animation meetings were usually scheduled,


427
00:20:30.145 --> 00:20:33.308
不仅频繁, 而且时间是早上6点
a lot of times, at 6:00 in the morning.


428
00:20:33.582 --> 00:20:37.882
所以, 我还记得早起开车去开会的情形
And so, yeah, I remember driving to go to those meetings.


429
00:20:38.020 --> 00:20:41.581
会场气氛通常有些奇怪
And then that sort of strange atmosphere at that time of the morning,


430
00:20:41.724 --> 00:20:43.885
大家都一副睡眼惺忪的样子
and hardly anyone is awake or around.


431
00:20:44.026 --> 00:20:47.826
后来他开始召集大家周日早上8点开会
He began calling meetings for 8:00 in the morning on Sunday.


432
00:20:47.963 --> 00:20:52.127
记得第二次参加的时候, 我受不了了
And I think it was about the second one, I was just angry.


433
00:20:52.267 --> 00:20:55.168
因为这简直是一种人格侮辱
Because it's just such a total sign of disrespect


434
00:20:55.304 --> 00:20:58.569
把一群才华横溢的员工当苦力使唤
for a lot of very talented people who are working their ass off for you.


435
00:20:58.707 --> 00:21:02.438
所以我说, 杰弗里, 我们得改个时间开会
And I said,"Jeffrey, we gotta have these meetings at some other time,


436
00:21:02.578 --> 00:21:06.207
我跟你说, 如果你再弄这么早
because I promise you, if you have another one of these things at 8 a.M.,


437
00:21:06.582 --> 00:21:09.312
我就穿着睡衣过来
I'm showing up in my pajamas."


438
00:21:10.486 --> 00:21:12.052
您感到骄傲吗, 迪斯尼先生?
Aren't you proud of it, Mr. Disney?


439
00:21:12.053 --> 00:21:13.978
何止骄傲, 我简直要膨胀了
Why, I'm so proud, I think I'll bust.


440
00:21:14.123 --> 00:21:15.750
时间差不多是…
I think it was right around the time of--


441
00:21:15.891 --> 00:21:18.189
奥斯卡颁奖那会儿… 就是那个时候
The Oscars were-- It was just around the corner.


442
00:21:18.327 --> 00:21:21.728
他说, 我对奥斯卡奖不感兴趣
And he said,"You know, I'm not interested in the Academy Awards.


443
00:21:21.864 --> 00:21:25.561
我只对钱感兴趣
I'm interested in the Bank of America awards," You know.


444
00:21:25.701 --> 00:21:27.396
我只在乎能赚多少钱
"What the money these things pull in."


445
00:21:27.536 --> 00:21:29.294
他这个观点
And it was just absolutely


446
00:21:29.295 --> 00:21:32.473
是艺术工作者们最反感的
the worst thing to tell a room full of artists.


447
00:21:32.608 --> 00:21:35.042
这令他们大失所望
It was so discouraging.


448
00:21:37.212 --> 00:21:39.009
一天, 杰弗里对我说
Jeffrey, one day, he said to me,


449
00:21:39.148 --> 00:21:41.776
你需要找个副手了
"You really need to get your own Jeffrey Katzenberg."


450
00:21:41.917 --> 00:21:44.408
我想了想说, 没错
And I began thinking and thinking, "You know, it's right.


451
00:21:44.553 --> 00:21:48.114
我不能总是亲历亲为, 毕竟能力也有限
I can't do this by myself and I'm not that talented anyway."


452
00:21:48.257 --> 00:21:50.725
